aces_container
------------------------------------------
This folder contains a reference implementation for an ACES container file
writer intended to be used with the Academy Color Encoding System (ACES). The
resulting file is compliant with the ACES container specification (SMPTE
S2065-4). However, there are a few things that are not demonstrated by this
reference implementation.

 * Stereo channels
 * EndOfFileFiller
 * Arbitrary attributes and naming validations
 * half type attributes
 * keycode value validations

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.30-1
  libAcesContainer0-1.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-4.9.0-1
  libstdc++6-4.9.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.24.51-4
  cmake-2.8.12.2-1
  cygport-0.16.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.0-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.0-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ampas/aces_container

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ampas/aces_container/archive/v1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack aces_container-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./aces_container-1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/aces_container-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/aces_container-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libAcesContainer0-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libAcesContainer-devel-1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

